## 🔬 4. Experiential & Project-Based Learning

### Engineering Clinics
*   Engineering Clinics are mandatory, project-based courses integrated into B.Tech programs.
*   Students form interdisciplinary teams to identify real-world technical or research problems.
*   Teams collaborate to design, build, and test working prototypes under the mentorship of faculty guides.
*   At the end of each semester, projects are showcased at the **Engineering Clinics Expo**, promoting practical innovation and technical presentations.

### Undergraduate Research Experience (URE)
*   Undergraduate students are encouraged to conduct research alongside faculty members.
*   The project outputs often result in patents or publication in international Scopus-indexed journals.
*   The research program is overseen by the Dean of Academic Research (Prof. Ravindra Dhuli).

