## 🎁 9. Merit Scholarships & Financial Aid

VIT-AP awards several scholarships to encourage academic excellence:

### I. STARS (Support The Advancement of Rural Students) Scholarship
A signature social welfare program providing **100% free higher education** to underprivileged rural students.
*   **Eligibility:**
    *   Must have completed Class 10 and 12 in **rural government schools** (excluding municipality/corporation area schools).
    *   Must be one of the top rankers (typically district toppers) in the Higher Secondary (Class 12) examinations.
    *   Must have studied Maths, Physics, and Chemistry (MPC group).
    *   Annual family income must be **below ₹1,50,000**.
    *   Limited to **one beneficiary per family**.
*   **Benefits:**
    *   100% Tuition Fee waiver.
    *   Free hostel room and mess food.
    *   Basic medical coverage.

### II. GV Merit Scholarship (UG Degrees)
*   Awarded to board toppers across the country.
*   Provides **100% tuition scholarship** for all years of the UG degree program (B.Com and B.A.).

### III. Tmt. Rajeswari Ammal Merit Scholarship (UG Degrees)
*   Awarded to district toppers across the country.
*   Provides **50% tuition scholarship** for the duration of the UG degree program.
*   If the district topper is a girl student, she receives an additional 25% waiver, making it a **75% scholarship**.

### IV. G.V. & Rajeswari PG Merit Scholarships
*   **100% Scholarship:** Awarded to PG non-engineering applicants (M.Sc. Physics, M.Sc. Chemistry) who secured a CGPA of 9.0 or 90%+ in their qualifying UG examination.
*   **50% Scholarship (75% for Girls):** Awarded to applicants with 8.0 to 8.9 CGPA in their UG qualifying exams.
*   **M.Sc. Data Science:** Candidates with a cumulative score of 90%+ in their UG degree get a 50% tuition fee concession.

